HEADWORD: Omphalomesenteric
<hw>Om`pha*lo*mes`en*ter"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Omphalo-</ets> + <ets>mesenteric</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the umbilicus and mesentery;
omphalomesaraic; <as>as, the <ex>omphalomesenteric</ex> arteries and
veins of a fetus</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
